<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[242,1474,1791,1850]" lastBlockId="26.[212,1444,266,463]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">
REMARKS. — This species was formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stewart" authorityYear="1930" box="[816,953,1793,1816]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Delectopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[816,953,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">Delectopecten</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="DIJKSTRA H. H." box="[1020,1174,1791,1815]" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" pagination="348 - 373" refId="ref26877" refString="DIJKSTRA H. H. 2001. - Bathyal Pectinoidea (Bivalvia: Propeamussiidae, Lawrence: 348 - 373." type="book chapter" year="2001">Dijkstra 2001</bibRefCitation>
). However, examination of Pliocene material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Seguenza" authorityYear="1877" box="[466,610,1826,1850]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Ciclopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="peloritanus">
<emphasis box="[466,610,1826,1850]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">C. peloritanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[668,714,1826,1850]" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Seguenza" authorityYear="1877" box="[837,951,1827,1850]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Ciclopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[837,951,1827,1850]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">Ciclopecten</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[1025,1073,1826,1850]" name="Italy" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">Italy</collectingCountry>
, indicates that the present species is morphologically closer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Seguenza" authorityYear="1877" box="[488,602,267,290]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Ciclopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[488,602,267,290]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">Ciclopecten</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<emphasis box="[690,834,267,290]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stewart" authorityYear="1930" box="[690,830,267,290]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Delectopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Delectopecten</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
It has similar commarginal undulations and antimarginal microsculpture. For a description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bavay" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[601,728,301,325]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Ciclopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fluctuatus">
<emphasis box="[601,728,301,325]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">C. fluctuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation author="DIJKSTRA H. H." box="[774,979,300,325]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" pagination="3 - 25" refId="ref26691" refString="DIJKSTRA H. H. 1995. - Bathyal Pectinoidea (Bivalvia: Propeamussiidae: regions. Nature and Culture 1: 3 - 25. Tokyo." type="journal article" year="1995">Dijkstra (1995: 51)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[212,1444,266,463]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">
The present specimen from the 
<collectingRegion box="[579,694,336,359]" country="French Polynesia" name="Iles Marquises" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">Marquesas</collectingRegion>
is similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[869,963,335,359]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">holotype</typeStatus>
from the Andaman Sea, but differs slightly in size (
<quantity box="[266,342,370,394]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
in height, 
<typeStatus box="[451,545,370,394]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[550,628,370,394]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
), sculpture of the left valve (fine radial sculpture, 
<typeStatus box="[1144,1238,370,394]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">holotype</typeStatus>
somewhat coarser) and the presence of delicate commarginal sculpture (nearly lacking in 
<typeStatus box="[957,1056,405,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">holotype</typeStatus>
). However, intermediate variants are also known (MNHN). Other characters are identical.
</paragraph>
